Introduction
The AiSocialNinja CLI is a powerful tool that allows users to interact with the AiSocialNinja platform directly from their terminal. It streamlines workflows for developers and power users.

Installation
To install the CLI globally via npm:

sh
npm install -g aisocialninja
Note: Node.js version 16 or above is recommended.

Getting Started
After installation, verify your CLI version:

sh
aisocialninja --version
To see available commands and options:

sh
aisocialninja --help
Available Commands
Command	Description	Example Usage
init	Initialize a new configuration	aisocialninja init
login	Authenticate your CLI session	aisocialninja login
post	Schedule or send a social post	aisocialninja post
status	View current status or recent activity	aisocialninja status
(Add/modify commands as per your CLI)

Examples and Use Cases
1. Initializing the CLI
sh
aisocialninja init
Follow the prompts to set up your configuration file.

2. Logging In
sh
aisocialninja login
Authenticate with your AiSocialNinja account securely.

3. Scheduling a Social Post
sh
aisocialninja post --message "Hello world!" --schedule "2025-06-19 09:00"
Schedule a post for your connected accounts.

Troubleshooting
Command Not Found: Ensure npm global bin is in your PATH.
Authentication Issues: Try running aisocialninja login again.
Permission Denied: Use sudo if necessary, but only when required.
FAQ
Q: Can I use the CLI without an AiSocialNinja account?
A: No, an active account is required for authentication.

Q: How do I update the CLI?
A: Run npm update -g aisocialninja to get the latest version.

